In this test, the participant is presented with sheets with 4 pictures. They are asked to point towards the picture representing one category (e.g. fruit: grape), then name it. After this, the participant has to recall the word. This is done for 16 words.  If they miss, they are told what the missing word was and promped to repeat it. After the learning, there is an interference (counting down from 100 by 3s. Then, there are 3 immediate recal trials where, in case of failure to recall one word, they are cued with the category of the missing words (e.g. what was the fruit?). There is a delayed recall after ~20 mins
Free score in the immediate recall (total of 3 trials, maximum is 48)
Total (Free + cued) score in the immediate recall (total of 3 trials, maximum is 48)
Free score in the delayed recall (out of 16)
Total (Free + cued) score in the delayed recall (out of 16)

A computerized task where faces are presented and identified with a name. Afterward, the participant has to recall the names associated with the faces. There is also a 20 mins delayed recall followed by a recognition where they have to if the name-face pair matches, if the name is new or if the name of another face was put there.
Same as immediate recall, but after a 20 mins delay.

1 = new name, 2 = same name-face pair as learned, 3 = name of another face on the wrong face. Correct : 2

The participant is presented auditorially with a list of 15 words. They have to recall them freely afterward. This is repeated 5 times for the learning phase (a1 to a5). As quickly as possible, the participant has to link characters following a specified order in 2 different trials: A consists in linking numbers in order. B consists in linking alternatively between letters and numbers in order (1-a-2-b-3-c-4-d etc.) A is to measure motor processing while B is for task switching. We usually subtract the time for B with the time for A.
Number of errors in trial A
Time for trial B (SUBTRACT WITH A)
Number of errors in trial B

This is a mini IQ test consisting of a verbal and a non-verbal reasoning subtests. Matrices is about completing an increasingly complex visual pattern with the correct option, and vocabulary is about correctly defining increasingly rare words.
Total score in the vocabulary subtest out of 59. The subjects can have either 0, 1(partial) or 2 points per item.
Total score in the matrix subtest out of 30. The subjects can have either 0 or 1 point pet item.
Sum of vocabulary and matrix t scores
Transformation of the sum of T scores into a scale with a mean of 100 with an SD of 15
